Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Liechtenstein. The Liechtenstein authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the authorities.
From 18 March, the border crossings at Schellenberg and Mauren will be closed, the border crossings at Ruggell and Schaanwald will remain open for commuters, goods traffic and transit. Further restrictions and inspections may be in operation. We advise travellers seeking to cross the border at Ruggell and Schaanwald to check the latest travel advice for Austria ahead of your journey. See Entry Requirements.
For information on how to return to the UK from Liechtenstein, see Return to the UK.
Gatherings of more than 5 people are banned. All restaurants, bars, leisure and entertainment facilities are closed.
Further information
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
